        "prose identifies the user as a nonprofit program manager",
        "prose preserves the impact-report cycle-time goal",
        "prose mentions beneficiary stories or beneficiary-quote work as a stated outcome",
        "prose does not hallucinate a second project (only impact-report-drafter exists in anecdotes)",
        "prose uses program/beneficiary language, not customer/user language",
        "prose stays under 400 words"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
